This paper deals with algorithms and complexity in the context of online bipartite matching, which is a problem in computer science and graph theory. The paper discusses the power of advice and randomization in solving this problem, which suggests that it belongs to the categories of data structures (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
